\[\frac{(A+3)x-(5A+6)}{(x-2)(x-5)}=\frac{Bx-11}{x^2-7x+10}.\]We can now set the numerators equal by comparing them, and we get $A+3=B, 5A+6=11$, and $x^2-7x+10=x^2-7x+10$.\end think <answer>$\mapsto$$\\ $
